---
title: "FIG. 4 — Synchronous Conflict Detection with Re-Read Verification"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as 400 — Agent
    participant CD as 410 — Conflict<br/>Detection Module
    participant VC as 420 — Version Control<br/>Repository
    participant H as 430 — Human

    A->>CD: 401 — Proposed spec artifact
    CD->>VC: 402 — Load upstream documents<br/>(product vision, architecture, brand)
    VC-->>CD: 403 — Upstream document content

    CD->>CD: 404 — Compare artifact<br/>against upstream

    alt 405 — CONFLICT detected
        CD-->>A: 406 — Block save.<br/>Identify violated constraint.
        A-->>H: 407 — "This contradicts<br/>[upstream constraint].<br/>Update upstream first."
        H->>A: 408 — "I've updated it"
        A->>VC: 409 — RE-READ upstream<br/>document from repository
        VC-->>A: 410 — Current document content

        alt 411 — Update confirmed
            A->>CD: 412 — Re-validate artifact
            CD-->>A: 413 — PASS
            A->>VC: 414 — Save artifact
        else 415 — Update NOT found
            A-->>H: 416 — "Update not detected<br/>in repository.<br/>Please commit the change."
        end

    else 417 — GAP detected
        CD-->>A: 418 — Allow save.<br/>Surface structured flag.
        A->>VC: 419 — Save artifact with GAP flag
        A-->>H: 420 — Surface gap for resolution

    else 421 — No issues
        CD-->>A: 422 — PASS
        A->>VC: 423 — Save artifact
    end
